# Core Orchestration

- Use `AGENTS.md` as the project briefing.
- Use `docs/agent-ops/requirements.md`, `plan.md`, `status-board.md`, and `decision-log.md` as the operational record.
- Keep changes small and traceable.
- Before claiming completion for meaningful work, run the relevant verification commands from `AGENTS.md`.
- If a task changes behavior or status, update the matching file in `docs/agent-ops/`.

# Approval and Boundaries

- Do not mark approval-sensitive work as done without explicit user approval.
- Ask before risky dependency additions, provider changes, schema changes, or destructive edits.
- Never commit secrets, `.env`, plaintext credentials, or local machine artifacts.

# Multi-Agent Pattern

- Use specialized subagents for context-heavy workstreams.
- Use frontend and backend subagents in parallel when the task can be split safely.
- Use the verifier subagent after implementation to challenge done-claims.
- Use the security subagent when touching credentials, external APIs, SMTP, or browser-visible settings.

